      "excerpt": "Thanks to new county funding, our engineering students now have access to modern oscilloscopes and PCB fabrication tools.",
      "content": "We are thrilled to announce the opening of our new Electronics Laboratory. Thanks to the support from the County Government of Kiambu, we have successfully installed modern diagnostic equipment, oscilloscopes, and PCB fabrication tools. This upgrade will significantly enhance the practical training for our Electrical and Electronics engineering students, ensuring they graduate with industry-standard skills that are highly sought after by employers across Kenya.\n\nThe lab will also be utilized for our upcoming short courses in mobile phone repair and advanced circuit board diagnostics.",
